DATA CLOUD
Snowflake Supported Regions for Data Cloud

Data Cloud supports integration with Snowflake in these regions.

United States and Canada
DATA CLOUD REGION	SNOWFLAKE CLOUD AND REGION
	Amazon Web Services (AWS)	Google Cloud Platform (GCP)	Microsoft Azure
AWS us-east-1 (Virginia)	us-west-2: US West (Oregon)	us-central1: US Central1 (Iowa)	westus2: West US 2
us-east-2: US East (Ohio)	us-east4: US East4 (N. Virginia)	eastus2: East US 2
us-east-1: US East (Virginia)	centralus: Central US (Iowa)
ca-central-1: Canada (Central)	southcentralus: South Central US (Texas)
canadacentral: Canada Central (Toronto)
Europe
DATA CLOUD REGION	SNOWFLAKE CLOUD AND REGION
	AWS	GCP	Microsoft Azure
AWS eu-central-1 (Frankfurt)	eu-west-1: Europe (Ireland)	europe-west2: Europe West2 (London)	uksouth: UK South
eu-west-2: Europe (London)	europe-west4: Europe West4 (Netherlands)	northeurope: North Europe
eu-west-3: Europe (Paris)	westeurope: West Europe
eu-central-1: Europe (Frankfurt)	switzerlandnorth: Switzerland North
eu-north-1: Europe (Stockholm)
Asia Pacific
DATA CLOUD REGION	SNOWFLAKE CLOUD AND REGION
	AWS	GCP	Microsoft Azure
AWS ap-northeast-1 (Tokyo)	ap-northeast-1: Asia Pacific (Tokyo)	Not available	
japaneast: Japan East (Tokyo)
southeastasia: Southeast Asia (Singapore)

ap-northeast-3: Asia Pacific (Osaka)	
southeastasia: Southeast Asia (Singapore)

Data Cloud within a specific region supports Snowflake-supported cloud platforms within that region and across other regions in the same continent. For example, Data Cloud in US East (Virginia) supports Snowflake-supported cloud platforms within the same region. It also supports other regions in the same continent, including US West (Oregon), South Central US (Texas), and Canada Central (Toronto).
